# Change Log

2026-07-10
- Release 10.2.1: bumped all version references (`Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.hardened`, `docker-compose.yml`, `build.sh`, `docker-image.yml`) from 10.2.0 to 10.2.1 to match `requirements.in`.
- Added `curl` to `Dockerfile` (default alpine image) and `Dockerfile-alpine.locked` via `apk add curl`. Left `Dockerfile-ubi.locked` alone (already has a working `curl` from the `curl-minimal` package kept for dnf/rpm) and left `Dockerfile-debian.locked`/`Dockerfile.hardened` alone (distroless, no package manager). Re-released the `10.2.1` tag/images to include this change.

2026-07-08
- Merged all 8 open Dependabot PRs: `parsedmarc` 9.11.2 -> 10.2.0, distroless/python3-debian13 and ubi9/python-312 base digest bumps, and 5 GitHub Actions version bumps (`docker/login-action`, `docker/metadata-action`, `docker/build-push-action`, `docker/setup-buildx-action`, `github/codeql-action`). The base-image bumps also resolved the `expat/libexpat1` CVE that was failing the scheduled Snyk Container Scan on the `locked-debian` image.
- Added a 14-day (`*/14 * *`) schedule to `build-locked-release` so the floating `alpine`/`debian`/`ubi` locked image tags get rebuilt against current base images even without a push to `main`. Pinned per-release version tags remain untouched/immutable.
- Fixed a stale hardcoded fallback (`9.2.1`) in `scheduled-secure-images`: it now resolves the latest published GitHub release dynamically when no version is supplied, and only pushes the floating `latest`/`distroless` tags (it was previously also repushing content under the immutable per-version tag on every scheduled run). Cadence changed from weekly to every 14 days.
- Release 10.2.0: bumped all version references (`Dockerfile`, `Dockerfile.hardened`, `docker-compose.yml`, `build.sh`, `docker-image.yml`) from 9.11.2 to 10.2.0 to match `requirements.in`.

2026-05-25
- Release 9.11.2: bumped all version references from 9.5.4/9.6.0 to 9.11.2 across Dockerfiles, docker-compose.yml, build.sh, requirements.in, and CI workflows.
- Consolidated and applied all 10 open Dependabot dependency bumps:
  * `parsedmarc` 9.6.0 -> 9.11.2 (requirements.in + lock rebuild) for latest fixes.
  * `urllib3` >=2.6.3 -> >=2.7.0 to pick up security patches.
  * Python base digest: `python:3-alpine3.23` -> `sha256:01f1254...` (Dockerfile, Dockerfile-alpine.locked).
  * Python slim base digest: `python:3.14-slim` -> `sha256:bc389f7...` (Dockerfile-debian.locked, Dockerfile.hardened).
  * distroless/python3-debian12 digest -> `sha256:7d1042c...` (Dockerfile-debian.locked, Dockerfile.hardened).
  * ubi9/python-312 digest -> `sha256:742c950...` (Dockerfile-ubi.locked).
  * GitHub Actions bumps:
    - `actions/upload-artifact` 7.0.0 -> 7.0.1 (build-locked-commit, build-locked-release, snyk-security).
    - `docker/build-push-action` 7.0.0 -> 7.1.0 (docker-build, docker-image, scheduled-secure-images, build-locked-commit, build-locked-release).
    - `sigstore/cosign-installer` 4.1.1 -> 4.1.2 (docker-build).
    - `github/codeql-action/upload-sarif` 4.35.1 -> 4.35.4 (trivy, snyk-security, snyk-container).
    - `aquasecurity/trivy-action` 0.35.0 -> 0.36.0 (trivy).
- Rationale: resolves accumulated Dependabot alerts for container base images, Python deps, and GitHub Actions security/tooling updates. Verified via `git diff --stat` showing 14 files changed, 33 insertions(+), 33 deletions(-).

2026-04-07
- Released `parsedmarc` 9.5.4: bumped Dockerfiles, compose, workflows, and requirements so base image and pull commands use the new version; tagged/published release for reproducible deployments.
- Hardened CI and release automation: added `production` environment with branch/tag policies and wired `build-locked-release` & `docker-build` to require it; recorded reasoning for traceability.
- Fixed automated scans: taught Trivy/Snyk release workflows to wait for published images before pulling so SARIF uploads (and the originating GitHub Code Scanning alerts) close reliably after new artifacts go live.
- Documented that Trivy alerts CVE-2026-30922 were cleared by regenerating `requirements.lock` with `pyasn1==0.6.3` inside the lockfile-based builds.
2026-04-07 (continued)
- Updated `Dockerfile-ubi.locked` so the ubi9/python-312 builder/runtime stages now point at `sha256:7ba356eca7f476bcf9a8c51714e43353376d37e0bbd4e43ceec7b1bcc6ff9675`, which carries Python 3.12.12-4.el9_7.2 and resolves CVE-2026-4519 identified by Trivy.
- Triggered `build-locked-release` on `main` after the base bump so the signed locked images rebuild from the patched UBI Python base, and explicitly reran the Trivy/Snyk published-image scans to refresh SARIF results against the new artifacts.
- Merged the pending Dependabot PRs for code scanning/sealing:
  * `sigstore/cosign-installer` to 4.1.1 and `github/codeql-action` to 4.35.1 so the signing and analysis workflows use the newest releases.
  * `docker/login-action` 4.1.0 plus the matching Docker workflow tweaks that rely on that action.
  * The `python` base digest bumps plus `parsedmarc==9.6.0` so the runtime is on the latest release while the locked images rebuild from the patched builder.
